sql: SELECT payments.amount, payments.order_id, payments.status, payments.id FROM payments WHERE payments.order_id IN (SELECT orders.id FROM orders);
SELECT orders.created_at, orders.status, orders.total, users.name, users.age FROM orders INNER JOIN users ON orders.user_id = users.id WHERE orders.created_at >= '2022-05-05';
SELECT created_at FROM notifications WHERE notifications.id >= 1292 ORDER BY notifications.read ASC, notifications.user_id ASC;
SELECT level, message, created_at FROM logs WHERE logs.message != 'value_960' ORDER BY logs.created_at ASC;

SELECT tasks.assignee_id, tasks.id, employees.hire_date, departments.name, departments.manager_id FROM tasks JOIN employees ON tasks.assignee_id = employees.id JOIN departments ON employees.department_id = departments.id WHERE departments.manager_id > 4340;
SELECT status FROM projects WHERE projects.end_date > '2025-07-20';
SELECT priority FROM tasks WHERE tasks.priority < 99 AND tasks.status != 'pending';
SELECT products.rating, categories.name, categories.id FROM products LEFT JOIN categories ON products.category_id = categories.id;
SELECT * FROM notifications;
SELECT id FROM shipping;
SELECT DISTINCT project_id FROM tasks;
SELECT inventory.warehouse_id, inventory.quantity, products.id, products.name FROM inventory JOIN products ON inventory.product_id = products.id WHERE inventory.updated_at > '2020-02-23';
SELECT rating, name FROM suppliers WHERE suppliers.rating > 4.1 AND suppliers.country >= 'FR';
SELECT payments.method, COUNT(id), COUNT(order_id) FROM payments WHERE payments.status >= 'inactive' GROUP BY payments.method;
SELECT orders.user_id, products.price, products.rating, inventory.quantity FROM orders INNER JOIN products ON orders.product_id = products.id JOIN inventory ON inventory.product_id = products.id;
SELECT tasks.project_id, tasks.due_date, COUNT(assignee_id), COUNT(id) FROM tasks GROUP BY tasks.project_id, tasks.due_date;
SELECT products.stock, categories.name, inventory.id, inventory.product_id FROM products JOIN categories ON products.category_id = categories.id JOIN inventory ON inventory.product_id = products.id;
SELECT customers.email, COUNT(name), COUNT(phone) FROM customers GROUP BY customers.email;
SELECT comments.body, comments.user_id FROM comments WHERE comments.user_id IN (SELECT users.id FROM users);
SELECT tasks.status, tasks.id, tasks.due_date, projects.end_date, projects.id FROM tasks JOIN projects ON tasks.project_id = projects.id WHERE tasks.assignee_id < 9910;

SELECT employees.id, departments.budget, departments.id FROM employees JOIN departments ON employees.department_id = departments.id WHERE employees.name <= 'value_723' AND employees.salary >= 2808.93;
SELECT * FROM sessions WHERE sessions.id < 3442;
SELECT reviews.user_id, reviews.rating FROM reviews WHERE reviews.user_id IN (SELECT users.id FROM users WHERE users.status < 'completed');
SELECT * FROM projects JOIN departments ON projects.department_id = departments.id WHERE projects.department_id = 4574 OR projects.status < 'cancelled';
SELECT id, description, name FROM categories WHERE categories.parent_id >= 9933;
SELECT inventory.warehouse_id, products.created_at, products.id FROM inventory INNER JOIN products ON inventory.product_id = products.id;
SELECT employees.name, COUNT(hire_date), COUNT(department_id) FROM employees GROUP BY employees.name;

SELECT tasks.priority, employees.department_id, projects.id, projects.name FROM tasks LEFT JOIN employees ON tasks.assignee_id = employees.id LEFT JOIN projects ON tasks.project_id = projects.id INNER JOIN departments ON employees.department_id = departments.id;
SELECT payments.status, payments.order_id, payments.method, orders.quantity, orders.user_id FROM payments JOIN orders ON payments.order_id = orders.id;
SELECT status, id FROM projects WHERE projects.status >= 'cancelled';
SELECT projects.budget, COUNT(end_date) FROM projects GROUP BY projects.budget HAVING COUNT(end_date) >= 58;
SELECT notifications.message, notifications.id, users.name, users.email FROM notifications LEFT JOIN users ON notifications.user_id = users.id WHERE notifications.user_id > 6276;
SELECT * FROM orders WHERE orders.created_at <= '2023-08-01' OR orders.id < 4893 LIMIT 100;
SELECT country FROM suppliers WHERE suppliers.country != 'DE';
SELECT id FROM comments WHERE comments.user_id >= 5364 OR comments.id > 7450 OR comments.entity_id < 5530 LIMIT 1000;
SELECT * FROM invoices;
SELECT * FROM shipping;
SELECT level, id, source FROM logs WHERE logs.id <= 6150 AND logs.created_at >= '2025-04-03' AND logs.level <= 'WARN';
SELECT body, entity_type, entity_id FROM comments WHERE comments.created_at < '2020-07-27';
SELECT products.category_id, products.stock, products.created_at, categories.description, categories.name FROM products INNER JOIN categories ON products.category_id = categories.id;
SELECT * FROM logs WHERE logs.created_at != '2023-06-01' ORDER BY logs.level ASC, logs.source ASC;
SELECT * FROM products WHERE products.stock > 89;
SELECT status, created_at, type FROM transactions WHERE transactions.created_at < '2023-12-18';
SELECT order_id, paid_at FROM payments WHERE payments.amount <= 2987.99 AND payments.status = 'inactive' ORDER BY payments.amount ASC;
SELECT * FROM tasks;

SELECT name, id, created_at FROM departments WHERE departments.manager_id >= 8057 AND departments.id = 9454 AND departments.created_at != '2025-01-05' ORDER BY departments.id ASC, departments.name ASC;
SELECT DISTINCT budget, status FROM projects WHERE projects.start_date >= '2022-10-20';
SELECT * FROM shipping WHERE shipping.id >= 7382;
SELECT payments.paid_at, payments.status, orders.quantity FROM payments JOIN orders ON payments.order_id = orders.id;

SELECT message, id, created_at FROM notifications WHERE notifications.created_at < '2024-09-16' AND notifications.message >= 'value_83' ORDER BY notifications.created_at DESC, notifications.type DESC;
